The paper discusses the design of hybrid beamformers for massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers the optimization of the beamformers, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of multiple antennas and RF chains is a common technique in multimedia systems (cs.MM), and the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms in terms of mean squared error (MSE), which is a common metric in machine learning (cs.LG).
